liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Woolworths boss Brad Banducci is warning of a tough consumer environment, but he hopes slowing inflation may mean lower supermarket prices. The supermarket giant posted a $1.62 billion profit for 2023. "Looking ahead to FY24, we expect food inflation in Australia and New Zealand to continue to moderate but will likely remain elevated in some packaged categories," Mr Banducci said. The supermarket chain is seeing higher rates of theft amid the high cost of living. Mr Banducci has told ABC senior business correspondent Peter Ryan that shoplifting has increased and organised gangs are stealing goods to resell.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Woolworth ceo says organised gangs stealing products

children.content: Woolworths boss Brad Banducci is warning of a tough consumer environment, but he hopes slowing inflation may mean lower supermarket prices.
The supermarket giant posted a $1.62 billion profit for 2023.
"Looking ahead to FY24, we expect food inflation in Australia and New Zealand to continue to moderate but will likely remain elevated in some packaged categories," Mr Banducci said.
The supermarket chain is seeing higher rates of theft amid the high cost of living.
Mr Banducci has told ABC senior business correspondent Peter Ryan that shoplifting has increased and organised gangs are stealing goods to resell.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The Australian share market has shrugged off a slow start and is trading up 0.7 per cent at midday. The ASX 200 is being driven by consumer stocks, banks, and miners after iron ore prices surged overnight. Technology stocks and healthcare firms are taking a hit. Woolworths is up 5.1 per cent after its posted a rise in profit. Domino's Pizza has surged despite a big fall in profit because it is cutting 200 jobs and restructuring. children.content: The Australian share market has shrugged off a slow start and is trading up 0.7 per cent at midday.
The ASX 200 is being driven by consumer stocks, banks, and miners after iron ore prices surged overnight.
Technology stocks and healthcare firms are taking a hit.
Woolworths is up 5.1 per cent after its posted a rise in profit.
Domino's Pizza has surged despite a big fall in profit because it is cutting 200 jobs and restructuring.
Here are the top movers:
IDP Education: +9.7 per cent to $25.53
Monadelphous: +9.4 per cent to $14.74
Domino's Pizza: +8.1 per cent to $51.92
WiseTech Global: -19.2 per cent to $70
Nanosonics: -9.2 per cent to $4.08
Illuka Resources: -7.4 per cent to $4.08

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Some other profit results out today: Logistics software company WiseTech Global saw net profit for 2023 rise by 9 per cent to $212 million. Its shares plunged because investors are disappointed by its forecast for 2024 earnings. Engineering firm Worley Parsons saw annual profit fall by 78 per cent to $37 million. IDP Education says net profit rose 45 per cent to $148.5 million for the year as student placement revenue increased to nearly $982 million as the international student market rebounded from COVID globally. Business travel management provider Corporate Travel Management says 2023 net profit rose from $3.2 million in 2022 to $77.6 million as revenue surged by 70 per cent as it gained new clients. But one of those clients is the United Kingdom, which is controversially paying CTM $3 billion to provide temporary housing for asylum seekers including on a barge in Dorset. "In April 2023, CTM was awarded its largest customer contract, to manage the accommodation needs of asylum seekers in the United Kingdom." "It is expected to contribute significantly to the Europe region's results in future years."
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Profit results
